items.name: Children's Books Wiki
items.title: Children's Books Wiki
items.headline: Children's Books Wiki
items.desc: Children's Books Wiki is a freely editable database about books written for children ages 0-16, and the young at heart. Each book has a description, readers' reviews, guidance on content, recommended reading age and suggestions for what to read next. Come and visit the only collaborative website dedicated to children's books!

items.name: Steve Cole Books Wiki
items.title: Steve Cole Books Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Steve Cole Wikia!
items.desc: This wiki focuses on the Astrosaurs children's series by British author Steve Cole, offering detailed information on the settings, characters, and objects found in its world. It also includes fun trivia, collectors' guides, and up to date real-world information on dinosaurs and other ancient animals.

items.title: Poison Apple Books Wiki
items.headline: Vampires, Curses, and Ghosts, Oh My! Introducing Poison Apple Books...
items.desc:
Are you ready to be creeped? Welcome to Poison Apple Books Wiki, where you can learn all about the Scholastic book series. Wether you are new to the series or a huge fan, there is something for everyone at this wiki.
· Write and contribute to articles
· Chat with your friends
· Can't find what you're looking for? Make it yourself!
I'm always looking for new potential rollback users and administrators, have fun!

items.name: Books of History Chronicles Wiki
items.title: Books of History Chronicles Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Ted Dekker Wiki
items.desc: The Ted Dekker Wiki is an encyclopedia of books written by Ted Dekker, New York Times Best Selling Author of over 20 novels. Dekker has worked in a variety of genres including fantasy, mystery, suspense, and horror. Some of his works include series such as The Circle Series, The Paradise Series, and The Lost Books Series. He has also written stand-alone novels such as Skin, House, and Immanuel's Veins.

items.name: Amelia's Notebooks Wiki
items.title: Amelia's Notebooks Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Amelia's Notebooks Wiki!
items.desc:
''Amelia's notebooks'' is a series of over thirty books written by Marissa Moss. They were once published by American Girl, better known for their dolls. The notebooks center around Amelia as she transitions through elementary and middle school.

Currently the wiki needs a lot of help with adding articles and cleaning up existing ones. Anyone is welcome to come and help!

items.name: Maria Wiki
items.title: Maria Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Crayla! Meet  the mexican girl named Maria!
items.desc: This wiki is about a mexican girl named Maria that moved from a island named Cotlind to a island named Crayla. She has all of wacky and crazy adventure and meets of all kinds of people, creatures, and family. Even though Maria is still a little sad about leaving Cotlind and her best friend, Kendal she still is happy to go to her home island.

items.name: Books of Enoch Wiki
items.title: Books of Enoch Wiki
items.headline: Examine and compare the books of Enoch.
items.desc: The books of Enoch are Jewish literary works attributed to the Biblical Enoch. This wiki explores, defines, and critiques each of the books attributed to Enoch... The Book of Enoch, The Book of the Secrets of Enoch, and The Revelation of Metatron. Welcome to this wiki to examine, compare, and comment on some of the most influential literary works in Judaism, Christology, and the occult.
